The suspense horror/dark fantasy story is set in Tokyo, which is haunted by mysterious "ghouls" who are devouring humans. People are gripped by the fear of these ghouls whose identities are masked in mystery. An ordinary college student named Kaneki encounters Rize, a girl who is an avid reader like him, at the café he frequents. Little does he realize that his fate will change overnight.
(Source: Anime News Network)

Thwarting a hijacking with the beautiful, silver-haired detective, Siesta, transforms Kimihiko’s young life. Their success kicks off years of crime-solving and confronting syndicates around the world—until Siesta dies. Left with questions, Kimihiko moves on. But now, a new case may open healed wounds as it connects to an assassin, a world conspiracy, and his dead partner! (Source: Funimation) Note: The first episode aired with a runtime of ~46 minutes as opposed to the standard 24 minute long episode.
Madousho Gakuen no Kinsho Shoujo: Shounen, Tomo ni Kinki wo Tsumugou ka
Ushiro no Seki no Gal ni Sukarete Shimatta. Mou Ore wa Damekamoshirenai

Sandai Fujiwara, a socially bottom-tier boy, sits in front of Shino Yuizaki, a beautiful gal at the top of the social caste.
Physically, they are very close to each other, but with their difference in status, it feels like they live in different worlds, never crossing paths with each other.
Until Sandai found Shino stuck in a ditch, having accidentally slipped.
“Thanks for the shower”
“Well, goodbye then.”
Although he takes Shino home on a whim to let her shower, Sandai remains wary of the gal. However, he finds himself increasingly attracted to Shino, who despite her looks, is actually not that experienced with men, even as she aggressively approaches him.
After some trouble, the two start dating, and begin to spend their days sweetly flirting with each other…….
